<HR><H2>database management package...</H2>
<H3>daemon@ATHENA.MIT.EDU (Tue Aug 15 00:05:38 1995
)</H3>
<PRE>
Date: Mon, 14 Aug 1995 22:03:56 -0600
From: 869683 Gillespie Brandon James &lt;brandon@hydepark.declab.usu.edu&gt;
To: coldstuff@MIT.EDU

Does anybody forsee any problem with switching the driver to use gnu's
dbm package, over the standard unix package?  The reason for this switch
is that there are a few os's which don't implement ndbm right, or buggy
(such as solaris), and centralizing on a readily available and free
package may help out some people...

(but it does mean more hassle in getting the driver off the ground)

-Brandon
</PRE>
